ormation be provided to debtors when entities are collecting certain debts. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. Any entity collecting or attempting to collect, directly or indirectly, debts owed or due or asserted to be owed or due another for any medical expense shall contact the debtor at least once in writing stipulating that the entity is contracted to collect on the obligation. The entity shall provide a copy of the claim, invoice, or bill with a summary of the charges owed by the debtor. If requested by the debtor, either orally or in writing, the entity shall provide a second written notice including the copy of the claim, invoice, or bill. 170 copies were printed on recycled paper by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.093 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 155, "action_date": "2013-01-16T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 23860, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/23860.pdf", "status_text": "First read in Senate and referred to", "journal_page": 116, "committee_id_action": 200, "committee_id_assigned": 177, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 155, "action_date": "2013-01-22T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 23942, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/23942.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for hearing", "journal_page": 0, "committee_id_action": 177, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 155, "action_date": "2013-01-22T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 24253, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/24253.pdf", "status_text": "Deferred to the 41st legislative day", "journal_page": 156, "committee_id_action": 177, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "P", "vote": {"vote_id": 12752, "president_vote": null, "Nay": [362], "Ye